<subSubSection id="913C6DF6AE594FE3E54C3023CF0B432E" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" type="description">
<paragraph id="CFDE277C7831D6B8CFDA046BC1D8DEAD" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D45719E16B1BA808E7B2F3DBE6EF9E25" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Perennial herb from a woody base, stems prostrate, reaching 50 cm, the whole plant densely villous. Leaves sessile, 2-4 
<normalizedToken id="3951674B0ECA9D61BD1078EDE5D1F10D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.4-1.3 cm, oblanceolate or oblong, becoming elliptic upwards, obtuse, margin entire, lower leaves attenuate at base, upper leaves and bracts cuneate, veins prominent, internodes short so leaves and flower heads more crowded than in related species. Inflorescence characteristically narrow, flowers 1-5 in subsessile, congested head-like scorpioid cymes; peduncle 0-1.5 cm; bracteoles 8-11 
<normalizedToken id="98B495B775320B0FD8F42C8D899AECFF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-5 mm, lanceolate to ovate, acute; pedicels absent; outer sepals 12-15 
<normalizedToken id="C4C0A38BB2E34486523981EB0B3D50C5" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, oblong, acuminate, flat; middle sepal asymmetric; inner sepals slightly shorter and narrower; corolla 2-2.8 cm long, usually creamy with a yellowish centre, weakly lobed, midpetaline bands long-sericeous; ovary and style glabrous, style divided 6 mm above base, stigmas 3mm; capsule glabrous, 1-seeded (fide 
<bibRefCitation id="069E187BA500CB0CA917E8308FE1E2FA" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="C50A15D2387CBE407BB594DB728E1FDC" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
); seeds glabrous. [
<bibRefCitation id="1FF46F0E5D7FFDED2E00C263CFA0143F" author="Sa'ad, F" journalOrPublisher="Bronder Offset, Rotterdam" pageId="210" pageNumber="211" pagination="1 - 287" refId="B314" refString="Sa'ad, F, 1967. The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht. Bronder Offset, Rotterdam: 1 - 287" title="The Convolvulus species of the Canary Isles, the Mediterranean region, and the Near and Middle East. Mededelingen van het Botanisch Museum en Herbarium van de Rijksuniversite Utrecht" year="1967">
<normalizedToken id="F3079414CAAACA69257784316D768AB4" originalValue="Sa’ad">Sa'ad</normalizedToken>
1967
</bibRefCitation>
: 168; 
<bibRefCitation id="A39A38C28E8DF77BB7C91BF5B1BADB57" author="Tohme, G" journalOrPublisher="National Council for Scientific Research, Beirut" pageId="213" pageNumber="214" pagination="1 - 609" refId="B363" refString="Tohme, G, Tohme, H, 2007. Illustrated Flora of Lebanon. National Council for Scientific Research, Beirut: 1 - 609" title="Illustrated Flora of Lebanon" year="2007">
<normalizedToken id="F40F994FEE72DE0207ED54C2BDC93EBE" originalValue="Tohmé">Tohme</normalizedToken>
and 
<normalizedToken id="2A746BB50A228CD0078150B06FF93F9B" originalValue="Tohmé">Tohme</normalizedToken>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
: 216 (photo)]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1E180A01083BADB6AD59F0C59E97E4C8" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D4E7B54517E4113A24CC300617193CFB" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1CCB2A25F141D6EF1FF19E601C3DDDDA" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Turkey (
<emphasis id="613A4D1F9632FA897B2B0641C9A1E793" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Uslu</emphasis>
1363, 2671); Syria (
<emphasis id="03912DF810309DC42E956EE3E4174BED" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Aucher-Eloy</emphasis>
1398); Lebanon (
<emphasis id="9D0331AF6CB1C96CE963F5A85F9C68F6" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Gombault</emphasis>
693, 
<emphasis id="DA6B9C5A13FC5E853FEEF0B12A592CF8" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Blanche</emphasis>
1457); Palestine/Israel (
<emphasis id="1D8D6666C039373F9CE734E6DC9EE2F6" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Eig &amp; Grizzi</emphasis>
369, 
<emphasis id="4B56701A90AE107FE68DB4C947D9B42D" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
<normalizedToken id="846B80FACDF8A006B0625B5C5BD9D0EB" originalValue="Bornmüller">Bornmueller</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
1108, 1109; 
<emphasis id="B325F54D737A561C50F530CC41114044" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Meyers &amp; Dinsmore</emphasis>
272; 
<emphasis id="C74E9AB5664D553126B95D116D686B42" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Davis</emphasis>
4424, 4672). On coastal sand. Records from Egypt are probably errors.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="73398D3EDCD3A910699DB3B7499AA560" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" type="notes">
<paragraph id="37DFF348F1EBF0C60D0026241F917E52" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB8E5ECDE6D1FC2B341F02F81F6F4AA7" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Unlike 
<taxonomicName id="57674CEE8C50995D257B5727FA812C72" authorityName="Vahl, Symb. Bot. 1: 16. 1790. (Vahl" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lanatus" order="Solanales" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanatus">
<emphasis id="662C06B6D9D5A8F54E91B18B5BB9FF50" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Convolvulus lanatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
this species appears to have long trailing stems, which may become somewhat woody when old, but it lacks the spinescent basal branches of 
<taxonomicName id="2F74DC28191B3E4D8B0D67B89C5C0E0C" authorityName="Vahl, Symb. Bot. 1: 16. 1790. (Vahl" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus lanatus" order="Solanales" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanatus">
<emphasis id="67700FDA94FBBAEF11CB76A58C5F11E3" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Convolvulus lanatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The sepals are also more shortly villous so the heads are more or less separate. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="A7AB72D07AC3CEAD1B124A629079AFC7" authorityName="Boiss., Diagn. Pl. Orient. 11: 81. 1849. (Boissier" authorityYear="1849" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus schimperi" order="Solanales" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schimperi">
<emphasis id="63AA0228DFAE79EE5A5EDC8A6E0D781A" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Convolvulus schimperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subsessile heads and leaves not undulate-margined and from 
<taxonomicName id="CAEE4CC701F78AC6BD48A5FC168AC36D" authorityName="Peter ex Hallier f., Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 18: 99. 1893 [&quot; 1894 &quot;]. (Hallier" authorityYear="1893" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus spicatus" order="Solanales" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="spicatus">
<emphasis id="B6FF21B99927D2118278853216FA42B1" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Convolvulus spicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the subsessile heads although short peduncles are clearly present in some specimens such as 
<emphasis id="FD9D1344B6ABF15FE60FAB8CADC4723B" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Melville</emphasis>
70/31 and 
<emphasis id="DB6CD9B72D8A3A35324885AA2FC68872" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Samuelson</emphasis>
527 (both K).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D13A8243792848DDE7B534CAAECCB1DF" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">
Species 178-181 are extremely similar and may prove to be conspecific. 
<taxonomicName id="B12D51A54B4DE161A57627ADEB515056" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus cephalodus" order="Solanales" pageId="184" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cephalodus">
<emphasis id="525D8E136D34F03D47C43A0BBE935D69" italics="true" pageId="184" pageNumber="185">Convolvulus cephalodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the hirsute ovary, but other distinctions are essentially minor differences of leaf shape. Clearly further collections are needed but not even the ovary indumentum is very convincing in the absence of other distinguishing characters.
</paragraph>
